  "text": "We use the arc-eager algorithm [CITATION_1] which is a bottom-up parsing strategy that is used in greedy and k-beam transitionbased parsers. One advantage of this strategy is that the words can get a head from their left side, before getting right dependents. This is particularly beneficial for our task, since we know that reparanda are similar to their repairs. Hence, a reparandum may get its head but whenever the parser faces a repair, it removes the reparandum from the sentence and continues its actions.",
